		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />So I would have to solder eight resistors, or one resistor pack on the converter between the male and female connectors.  As I have a Famicom, I don't really have much of a use for my Famicom to NES converter.  (I like to use it with Famicom games with internal sound chips in them to demonstrate what happens when the sound chip can't receive/send the sound from/to the cart.)  Would this ruin the converter for uses other than dumping cartridges?

		

