	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>kevtris</b> [ Tue Nov 15, 2005 1:04 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">DrNES wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">On your site you state that...<br /><br />"The original prototype had an LCD display on it, but this was deemed redundant so I removed it."<br /><br />Meaning you removed this function from the PCB design itself or in the software?<br /><br />Is it still possible to incorperate an LCD display into the current CopyNES design? Even if one would have to tap signals or sources from components on the CopyNES PCB itself.<br /><br />Thanks.</div>
<br />
<br />The place on the PCB is still there if you feel the need to mount an LCD connector and hook it up.  The code still drives it technically.  It has a 14 pin connector outline made to take a 2 by 7 pin header for a 14 pin ribbon cable to the display.  Pinout matches an LCD.  Note that the LCD's ENABLE line is being used for flash ROM carts... this won't affect anything of value though.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
